* An alternate date for the [[Awakening of Men|Awakening]] of [[Men]], the Secondborn [[Children of Ilúvatar]], in [[Hildórien]], according to the [[Round World version of the Silmarillion|Round World version]] of ''[[The Silmarillion]]''.<ref>{{NM|Awaking}}, p. 43</ref><ref group="note">In this particular conception, [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] moved the date of the [[Awakening of the Elves]] to {{YT|1000}}, as opposed to {{YT|1050}} in accordance with the timeline from ''[[The Annals of Aman]]'' and ''[[The Grey Annals]]'', while the length of a single Valian Year here was equal to 144 [[Years of the Sun|solar years]] (which is the length of a ''[[yén]]'', an Elvish 'long-year'). This means that the race of Men existed upon [[Ambar|Earth]] for 61,510 solar years by the time of the arrival of the [[Edain]] to [[Beleriand]] in {{YS|310}}.</ref>

